---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What is a good budget for a gaming laptop?",
    a: "A good budget for a gaming laptop depends on your needs. Entry-level laptops start under $1000, mid-range is $1000-$1500, high-end is $1500-$2000, and premium models are $2000+."
  },
  {
    q: "Is the RTX 5060 enough for 1440p gaming?",
    a: "Yes, the RTX 5060 provides excellent performance for 1440p gaming in most modern titles, though you might need to lower some settings in the most demanding games to maintain high frame rates."
  },
  {
    q: "Are gaming laptops upgradable?",
    a: "Generally, you can upgrade the RAM and storage (SSD) on most gaming laptops. However, the CPU and GPU are usually soldered to the motherboard and cannot be upgraded."
  },
  {
    q: "How important is the display refresh rate?",
    a: "For competitive gaming, a high refresh rate (144Hz, 240Hz, or higher) is crucial for smooth motion and reduced input lag. For casual gaming, 60Hz to 120Hz is often sufficient."
  },
  {
    q: "Do gaming laptops overheat?",
    a: "Gaming laptops can get quite hot under heavy load due to their compact size. Proper ventilation, using a cooling pad, and regularly cleaning dust from the fans can help manage thermals."
  }
];

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best Gaming Laptops 2026",
    "description": "Discover the best gaming laptops of 2026 across all budgets. Compare GPUs, CPUs, displays, and more to find the perfect laptop for you.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Leeroy Jenkins"
    },
    "datePublished": "2026-08-15",
    "dateModified": "2026-08-15"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": f.a
      }
    }))
  }
];

export const meta = {
  title: "Best Gaming Laptops 2026",
  description: "Discover the best gaming laptops of 2026 across all budgets. Compare GPUs, CPUs, displays, and more to find the perfect laptop for you.",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="leeroyjenkins"
  title="Best Gaming Laptops 2026"
  description="Discover the best gaming laptops of 2026 across all budgets. Compare GPUs, CPUs, displays, and more to find the perfect laptop for you."
  canonical="https://leeroyjenkins.quest/best-gaming-laptops-2026"
  schema={JSON.stringify(schema)}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Best Gaming Laptops 2026</h1>
      <p>Discover the best gaming laptops of 2026 across all budgets. Compare GPUs, CPUs, displays, and more to find the perfect laptop for you.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="content-section">
      <p>Finding the right gaming laptop requires balancing performance, display quality, thermals, and budget. Here is our comprehensive guide to the best gaming laptops in 2026.</p>

      <h2>Top Gaming Laptops by Budget</h2>

      <div class="tier-grid">
        <div class="tier-card">
          <h3>Under $1000</h3>
          <p>Great entry-level performance for 1080p gaming.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Acer Nitro:</strong> Solid build, good value, entry-level GPUs.</li>
            <li><strong>Lenovo IdeaPad Gaming:</strong> Clean aesthetic, reliable performance.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card highlight">
          <h3>$1000 - $1500</h3>
          <p>The sweet spot for performance and value, often featuring RTX 5060 GPUs.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>ASUS TUF:</strong> Durable design, excellent battery life.</li>
            <li><strong>HP Victus:</strong> Sleek look, solid 1080p/1440p performance.</li>
            <li><strong>Lenovo Legion 5:</strong> Top-tier cooling, excellent display options.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card">
          <h3>$1500 - $2000</h3>
          <p>High-end performance for high refresh rate 1440p gaming.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Razer Blade 15:</strong> Premium aluminum chassis, thin and light.</li>
            <li><strong>MSI Katana:</strong> Powerful internals, focused on pure gaming performance.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card">
          <h3>Premium ($2000+)</h3>
          <p>No-compromise performance, top-tier displays, and premium build quality.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>ASUS ROG:</strong> Innovative designs, top-tier cooling, best-in-class screens.</li>
            <li><strong>Alienware:</strong> Distinctive design, massive power, premium support.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Key Features to Compare</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>GPU:</strong> The most important component. Options range from the RTX 5060 (excellent for 1080p/1440p) up to the mighty RTX 5090 (for 4K and max settings).</li>
        <li><strong>CPU:</strong> Intel Core i7/i9 or AMD Ryzen 7/9 ensure your GPU isn't bottlenecked and provide excellent multi-tasking performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Display:</strong> Look for a balance of refresh rate (144Hz+ for smooth gaming), response time (3ms or lower), and panel type (IPS for color accuracy, OLED for incredible contrast).</li>
        <li><strong>Battery:</strong> Gaming laptops drain batteries quickly while gaming. Look for larger batteries (80Wh+) if you need portability for non-gaming tasks.</li>
        <li><strong>Weight:</strong> Lighter laptops (under 4.5 lbs) are easier to carry but may sacrifice cooling or performance compared to thicker desktop replacements.</li>
        <li><strong>Thermals:</strong> Effective cooling is critical to prevent thermal throttling. Look for laptops with robust vapor chambers or multiple heat pipes.</li>
        <li><strong>Upgradability:</strong> Ensure the laptop allows easy access to upgrade RAM (SO-DIMM slots) and storage (M.2 NVMe slots).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      {faqs.map(f => (
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>{f.q}</h3>
          <p>{f.a}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 650px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.5; }

    .content-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .content-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; }
    .content-section h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
    .content-section p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .content-section ul { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }
    .content-section li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    strong { color: var(--text-primary); }

    /* Tiers */
    .tier-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .tier-card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; }
    .tier-card.highlight { border: 2px solid var(--accent-color); position: relative; }
    .tier-card h3 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .tier-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .tier-card ul { padding-left: 1rem; margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    .tier-card li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }

    /* FAQ */
    .faq-item { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
    .faq-item h3 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .faq-item p { margin-bottom: 0; }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .hero h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
